title: Democrats win major US votes as California joins 'gerrymandering arms race' | ABC NEWS
description: Millions of Americans have cast their vote in elections for governors, mayors and ballot measures across the country. The Democrats secured major victories with governors in Virginia and New Jersey, mayor in New York City, and a new congressional map for California. The redraw of California's electoral boundaries has given the Democrats a chance at winning as many as five additional seats. As Chief Elections Analyst Casey Briggs explains, it's a move that comes after the Republicans' Texas redraw, marking a 'gerrymandering arms race' for the United States.
